                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 837.00/1176½</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-03-04T00:00:00-05:29">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 4, 1917, midnight</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your March 2, 4 p.m. The President promises desired action opening of and issuing
                    clearance to ships at earliest possible date consistent with military necessity.
                    He does not wish munitions to reach rebels before he can get forces to city.
                    Also desires to bar their escape and avoid further looting customs receipts.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gonzales</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
